@startuml sie-emergence-state-machine-v1

' ============================================================
' VISUAL THEME
' ============================================================

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam ArrowColor #57606A
skinparam DefaultFontName "SansSerif"
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8C5
skinparam noteBorderColor #57606A

skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #F6F8FA
  BorderColor #57606A
  FontColor #24292F
}

title SIE - Emergence Lifecycle State Machine - v1

' ============================================================
' EMERGENCE LIFECYCLE
'
' Goal: track the systemic process of **Emergence** (second-order definitional
' change) in the Definition Plane, initiated by evidence coming from the
' Description Plane.
'
' Non-goal: initial population of definitions.
' - During SIE deployment/bootstrap, definitions are seeded/synchronized from
'   authoritative sources (repos/CMDB/directories). This is handled by a
'   Definition Population process and MUST NOT be treated as emergence.
'
' Homeostasis vs Emergence decision point:
' - If mismatch is resolvable by regulation/action within current definitions,
'   homeostasis handles it and emergence is NOT opened.
' - If mismatch indicates a *variety deficit* / missing definition capability,
'   emergence is opened to propose definition changes.
'
' Note on terminology:
' - **Adaptation** is reserved for rule-level change within existing policy
'   bounds (behavioral reconfiguration).
' - **Emergence** is reserved for changes to Policies / structural primitives /
'   constraint-structure (governed second-order change).
' ============================================================

[*] --> OPEN : create(Emergence)

state OPEN {
}

OPEN --> DIAGNOSING : trigger received
note on link
  Trigger sources include:
  - Observation (document/intent)
  - Coherence escalation
  - Definition–Description mismatch
  - Explicit user request
end note

DIAGNOSING --> CANCELLED : homeostatic resolution applicable
note on link
  Condition: mismatch classified as solvable
  by remediation/tuning under current policies/rules.
end note

DIAGNOSING --> PROPOSING : classified as "definition change needed"
note on link
  Condition examples:
  - Variety deficit (NOT_FEASIBLE)
  - Missing primitive / missing scope concept
  - Persistent semantic drift requiring new policy/rule
end note

PROPOSING --> VERIFYING : proposal assembled

VERIFYING --> PROPOSING : incoherent but refinable
note on link
  Condition: coherence/feasibility checks return issues
  and auto-refinement is enabled.
end note

VERIFYING --> FAILED : incoherent / unsafe / cannot refine

VERIFYING --> AWAITING_APPROVAL : coherence OK + impact assessed

AWAITING_APPROVAL --> REJECTED : governance decision == reject
AWAITING_APPROVAL --> APPROVED : governance decision == approve
AWAITING_APPROVAL --> CANCELLED : timed out / withdrawn

APPROVED --> ENACTING : execution plan created

ENACTING --> STABILIZING : definition changes applied
note on link
  Condition: primitives created/deprecated + policies/rules published
  + downstream compilation/indexing completed.
end note

STABILIZING --> STABILIZED : mismatch reduced and stable
note on link
  Condition: observed mismatch signal converges
  (e.g., below threshold for N windows) AND
  no new incoherence introduced.
end note

STABILIZING --> FAILED : rollback triggered or instability persists

REJECTED --> [*]
CANCELLED --> [*]
FAILED --> [*]
STABILIZED --> [*]

note right of DIAGNOSING
  **Definition–Description mismatch (evidence)**
  A mismatch is *activable information* (error signal) describing
  a gap between:
  - Definition plane expectations (schemas, constraints, references)
  - Description plane availability/observability (state objects, events)

  Typical types:
  - VALUE_DEVIATION (violations/drift)
  - COVERAGE_GAP (missing sourced state object/event)
  - SCHEMA_DRIFT (source no longer matches archetype)
  - REFERENCE_GAP (definition refers to non-existent primitive)
  - VARIETY_DEFICIT (constraint not feasible with existing mechanisms)

  Only some types require emergence (policy/primitives/constraint-structure change).
end note

@enduml
